id: jf-ss2e
title: Make release changelog validation target-version aware
description: "The first production Auto Release run generated a versioned changelog, then the generic changelog check regenerated the pending Unreleased form and rejected the otherwise valid release workspace."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: automation,changelog,regression,release
created_at: "2026-07-21T18:06:26.555Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T18:09:25.442Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T18:08:06.719Z"
author: codex-release-agent
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "Normal main-branch changelog checks continue to validate the Unreleased form.; Release preparation validates the generated target-version form without drift.; The real Auto Release run publishes and verifies the exact package through npm, npx, and Bun."
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Remove the final production-only release blocker.
impact: Allows deterministic automated publishing after all quality gates pass.
outcome: One changelog check supports both pending and release-preparation contexts explicitly.
why_now: The production exercise exposed a context mismatch that local pending-state validation could not reproduce.
parent: jf-tike
reviewer: maintainer
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: release-hardening
release: 2026.7.21
severity: high
environment: GitHub Actions release workspace
repro_steps: "Generate the changelog with a target release version, then run the generic pending-state changelog check."
resolution: Added a target-aware changelog check helper and passed the target version only into release-preparation validation while retaining pending-state validation by default.
expected_result: The release gate validates the exact target-version changelog.
actual_result: Node and Bun regression tests plus an isolated clean-clone dual-context changelog check passed; the production rerun remains the final publication proof.
affected_version: 2026.7.16
fixed_version: 2026.7.21
component: release-automation
regression: true
customer_impact: No package was published; automated releases were blocked safely.
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T18:08:05.650Z",codex-release-agent,"Isolated clean-clone proof passed both modes: an unset target validated the pending Unreleased changelog, while PM_CHANGELOG_RELEASE_VERSION=2026.7.21 validated the prepared versioned changelog generated from the same closed pm items."
  "2026-07-21T18:09:25.441Z",codex-release-agent,"Final local gate passed after closure and changelog regeneration: 28 closed items have complete resolution metadata; 30 history streams have zero drift; 895 tests passed with 177 credential-dependent skips and zero failures; build, pack, npm/npx, Bun, changelog, and secret scans all passed. Preservation comparison found all 27 prior generated bullets present plus the new fix entry."
